{
  "name": "Google Calendar Sync",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Before running this\n\n1. Create an **HTTP Header Auth** credential named `Webhook Secret`:\n   - Header Name: `X-Webhook-Secret`\n   - Header Value: same value as al-quotes' `WEBHOOK_SECRET` env var\n2. Assign that credential to: **Webhook**, **Callback: Linked**, **Callback: Unlinked**\n3. Replace the placeholder URL in **Callback: Linked** and **Callback: Unlinked** with your real al-quotes URL, e.g. `https://<your-al-quotes-domain>/webhooks/n8n/calendar-sync`\n4. Activate the workflow, copy the **production** webhook URL from the **Webhook** node, and set it as al-quotes' `CALENDAR_WEBHOOK_URL` env var\n\nHabit events get a default 1-hour block starting at the moment the workflow runs, repeating via RRULE \u2014 adjust the expression in **Insert Event** / **Patch Event** if you want a fixed time of day instead.",
        "height": 532,
        "width": 460
      },
      "id": "659fef60-fe9d-4a2d-aa25-b795e2755964",
      "name": "Read Me",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1280,
        -624
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "boolean": [
            {
              "value1": "={{ $json.body.action.includes('upserted') }}",
              "value2": true
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "6df17622-dfe3-4a30-89c9-e42fff3c6056",
      "name": "Is Upsert?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -192,
        160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "language": "javaScript",
        "jsCode": "const body = $input.item.json.body;\n\nlet start;\nlet end;\nif (body.entityType === 'task') {\n  start = body.task.startDate || body.task.dueDate;\n  end = body.task.dueDate || body.task.startDate;\n} else if (body.entityType === 'event') {\n  start = body.event.startAt;\n  end = body.event.endAt ?? body.event.startAt;\n} else {\n  start = new Date().toISOString();\n  end = new Date(Date.now() + 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();\n}\n\nfunction resolveTimeZone(dateTime) {\n  const match = /(Z|[+-]\\d{2}:\\d{2})$/.exec(dateTime || '');\n  if (!match) return 'UTC';\n  if (match[1] === 'Z') return 'Etc/UTC';\n\n  const [, sign, hh, mm] = /^([+-])(\\d{2}):(\\d{2})$/.exec(match[1]);\n  if (mm !== '00') return 'UTC';\n\n  const hours = parseInt(hh, 10);\n  if (hours === 0) return 'Etc/UTC';\n\n  // Etc/GMT signs are inverted by POSIX convention: +07:00 -> Etc/GMT-7\n  const invertedSign = sign === '+' ? '-' : '+';\n  return `Etc/GMT${invertedSign}${hours}`;\n}\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    ...$input.item.json,\n    resolvedStart: start,\n    resolvedEnd: end,\n    resolvedTimeZone: resolveTimeZone(start),\n  },\n};\n"
      },
      "name": "Resolve Sync DateTime",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "id": "c7b61c7a-e9a2-4da7-ab26-d14babd65ee9",
